HEADWORD: Embattlement
<hw>Em*bat"tle*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An
intended parapet; a battlement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The fortifying of a building or a wall by means of
battlements.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Embay</ent>⟦br⟧
